<HEADLINE>
<P>
DWP BILL DISPUTE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 At age 76, I have just discovered the meaning of "you can't fight City Hall." 
</P>
<P>
 Our company has been in business in Los Angeles since 1923.For many years our 
electric bills have averaged $40,000 per month. Recently, we had a difference 
of opinion with the Department of Water and Power amounting to $3,300. We went 
to Small Claims Court to present ourcase. 
</P>
<P>
 It was our understanding that no attorneys are to represent either side in 
Small Claims Court; citizen against citizen, right? Wrong! We were in court on 
Dec. 5, and the DWP was a no-show. DWP merely sent a letter to the judge from 
the Los Angeles city attorney and that was enough to lose our case. 
</P>
<P>
 Thanks, Los Angeles. Perhaps we should have sued for millions. 
</P>
<P>
 HAIG DULGARIAN 
</P>
<P>
 Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
