<HEADLINE>
<P>
ADOPTION PROGRAMS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 As executive director of Holy Family Services, Counseling and Adoption, I must 
really protest the statement made in the Robert Scheer Column Left, "Returning 
to Bad Old Days of Orphanages" (Dec. 11). 
</P>
<P>
 I am bothered by the erroneous statement, "Vista del Mar runs the only 
licensed adoption program in Los Angeles County."This is not true. 
</P>
<P>
 Holy Family Services has been providing quality licensed adoption and foster 
care services in Los Angeles and Orange counties since our inception in 1949. 
In addition, we belong to the California Assn. of Adoption Agencies, which is 
an umbrella group for many licensed adoption agencies both in Los Angeles 
County and statewide. 
</P>
<P>
 It is often very difficult to get attention paid to the field of adoption in 
the press. To omit all other adoption agencies such as ourselves doing this 
good and vital work is an omission that cannot go uncorrected. 
</P>
<P>
 DAVID BALLARD 
</P>
<P>
 Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
