<TEXT>
<P>
 House of Fabrics Lists Pretax Charges: The Sherman Oaks-based fabrics and 
crafts retailer said it had costs of as much as $69 million in the third 
quarter because of store closings and deep discounts on its inventory.House of 
Fabrics Inc., which recently sought Chapter 11 protection from creditors in 
Bankruptcy Court, said it will take pretax charges of up to $50 million to 
cover the cost of closing more than 200 stores, and a $19-million pretax loss 
provision because of steep markdowns. The company didn't say what the after-tax 
effect on third-quarter earnings would be. Sales for the quarter ended Oct. 31 
fell 36% to $90.6 million. 
