<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE WEEK AHEAD: VATICAN CITY; RITES OF THE SEASON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In the annual celebration of Christmastide, Pope John Paul II will conduct the 
traditional Mass on Sunday morning at St. Peter's, the largest church in 
Christendom, in the midst of a busy weekend of activities. Later that day, 
speaking from the central balcony of St. Peter's, the Roman Catholic pontiff 
will deliver his annual blessing entitled "Urbi et Orbi," or "To the City and 
the World." 
</P>
<P>
 The Pope's seasonal ceremonies commence on Thursday when he tenders Christmas 
greetings to the cardinals, the pontifical family and the Curia at the Sala 
Clementina of the Apostolic Palace of the Vatican. At midnight Saturday, he 
will conduct the midnight Mass at St. Peter's, at the altar where only a Pope 
can say Mass. 
</P>
<P>
 Polish-born John Paul is the first non-Italian Pope in 4 1/2 centuries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
