<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY ALMANAC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Huntington Beach officials are taking a serious look at the Police Department. 
</P>
<P>
 The Police Department has 230 sworn officers. 
</P>
<P>
 During the past decade, Huntington Beach's population has increased from 
180,000 to about 190,000.During that same period, the city's ratio of police 
officers per 1,000 residents increased from 1.1 to 1.2, but it is still below 
the national average of 2.2. 
</P>
<P>
 Also during this 10-year period, calls for service increased 54%, from 75,898 
to 116,727 a year. 
</P>
<P>
 City officials hoped to hire six new officers and a sergeant soon. But the 
bond crisis might put those plans on hold. Today 
</P>
<P>
 Put on your dancing shoes. 
</P>
<P>
 Here's a chance to learn some dancing moves and meet new people at the same 
time. 
</P>
<P>
 The Singles Swing and Ballroom Dance Club meet at 7:30 p.m. at 3100 E. Coast 
Highway in Corona del Mar. 
</P>
<P>
 Lessons include country, West Coast swing and Latin dancing, among others. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information about the club, you can call (714) 494-0593. 
</P>
<P>
 The club meets regularly. Dues are $28 per month. 
</P>
