professional development group that includes executives from 100 chambers in 
the region. 
</P>
<P>
 * An Encino stockbroker received a one-month suspension from the National 
Assn. of Securities Dealers and a $5,000 fine, the NASD said. 
</P>
<P>
 Robert Alan Grunburg received the sanctions after allegedly approving two 
newspaper ads that contained misleading or exaggerated statements concerning 
the ranking of mutual funds. Grunburg and another broker also failed to file 
the ads with the NASD within the required 10-day limit, the NASD said. 
</P>
<P>
 Before resuming associations with any NASD member, Grunburg must requalify by 
examination. 
