<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL ROUNDUP: INSURANCE AUTO AUCTIONS BUYS COMPANY IN ATLANTA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Insurance Auto Auctions Inc., a North Hollywood company that sells salvaged 
vehicles for automobile insurance companies, said it has acquired an 
Atlanta-based company that performs the same service. 
</P>
<P>
 The acquired company, East Atlanta Group Inc., sells about 5,000 vehicles per 
year throughout Georgia, Insurance Auto Auctions said. Terms of the purchase 
were not disclosed. Both companies serve automobile insurance companies by 
selling badly damaged or recovered stolen vehicles -- so-called "total loss" 
vehicles. 
</P>
<P>
 Insurance Auto Auctions also said the Hertz Corp. car rental company has 
signed an agreement naming Insurance Auto Auctions the preferred provider of 
automotive salvage services for Hertz nationwide. 
</P>
</TEXT>
