<HEADLINE>
<P>
JOHN R. WOODEN CLASSIC TO RETAIN NAME FOR 1995 EVENT AT THE POND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE DiGIOVANNA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The second John R. Wooden Classic will be at The Pond of Anaheim in 1995 with 
the former UCLA basketball coach's name continuing as part of the event, a 
tournament organizer said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 Though the Dec. 3 event was a success with a crowd of 18,307, there have been 
reports that Wooden was uncomfortable with the halftime tribute and how 
proceeds from the event were disbursed -- he reportedly wanted more given to 
charities. 
</P>
<P>
 But the two sides apparently ironed out their differences. 
</P>
<P>
 "Though there were some minor misunderstandings recently, they're going to 
move ahead with the coach's name attached to the event," said Todd Lieman, 
spokesman for Irvine-based Hill and Knowlton, which managed the event. MIKE 
DiGIOVANNA 
