<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD IN BRIEF; IRAQ; U.S. AWACS OFFICER FACES COURT-MARTIAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The U.S. Air Force said Capt. Jim Wang will face a court-martial for his role 
as chief of the crew on the AWACS plane that failed to warn off two F-15s that 
shot down two U.S. helicopters over Iraq last April, killing 26.Charges against 
four other AWACS officers were dismissed. The Air Force had earlier dropped 
charges against the pilots of the F-15s that blew the two helicopters out of 
the air over northern Iraq. The accident killed 15 Americans, six military 
officers from Britain, France and Turkey and five Kurdish workers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
