<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A small airplane departing a San Bernardino Mountains airport crashed in a 
field Monday, killing two people and injuring one, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 The single-engine plane went down half a mile east of Big Bear City Airport, 
said San Bernardino County Sheriff's Deputy Jim Kuck. 
</P>
<P>
 The victims were not identified. The injured person was flown to a hospital. 
There was no immediate report on that person's condition. 
</P>
<P>
 A fire broke out but was contained to the crash site, the deputy said. 
</P>
<P>
 The type of airplane was not known. 
