 Northrop Grumman Wins Navy Contract: The Navy awarded Northrop Grumman a 
$122.5-million contract for long-lead procurement and production start-up for 
seven new E-2C Hawkeye airborne early warning and command and control 
aircraft.Navy plans call for full production contracts for the Group II 
Hawkeyes, the latest version of the radar aircraft, to be authorized and 
awarded under the 1995 and '96 budgets. Four aircraft will be delivered in 1997 
and three in '98, the company said in a news release. Total value for the 
