<P>
 Liz Claiborne to Shut Some Stores: The apparel maker said it will close its 
77-store First Issue retail chain, which includes stores in Costa Mesa, San 
Diego, Canoga Park, Santa Monica and Arcadia. First Issue stores sell women's 
casual and career clothes under the First Issue name, but the label failed to 
catch on, the firm said.The stores will be closed or converted to Liz 
Claiborne, Dana Buchman and Elisabeth stores. Executives didn't know how many 
stores will be converted or how many of the chain's 500 to 600 employees will 
lose their jobs. The New York-based company said it will take a pretax charge 
against earnings of $20 million to $30 million, cutting 16 cents to 24 cents 
from fourth-quarter net income. 
