<HEADLINE>
<P>
BMW TO MAKE ENGINES FOR ROLLS-ROYCES; AUTOS: THE DEAL, A COUP OVER BMW RIVAL 
MERCEDES-BENZ, MARKS THE END OF AN ERA FOR ROLLS. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Germany's BMW trumped its arch-rival Mercedes-Benz Monday by signing a deal 
with Rolls-Royce Motor Cars that will put BMW engines in the world's most 
prestigious cars. 
</P>
<P>
 The coup over Mercedes marks the end of a high-profile year for BMW that began 
with its controversial acquisition of Britain's last British-owned high-volume 
car manufacturer, Rover Cars, from British Aerospace. 
</P>
<P>
 The Rolls-BMW deal marks the end of an era for Rolls-Royce, whose cars convey 
the rich and the royal the world over. It has been making its own engines since 
1904. 
</P>
<P>
 The link will save Vickers PLC, the engineering company that owns Rolls-Royce, 
the cost of developing new engines for badly needed revamps of the Rolls-Royce 
line. 
</P>
<P>
 The engines in current Rolls-Royce models have not been updated since the 
1950s. 
</P>
<P>
 "We did of course fully exploit the competitive position (between the two 
German companies)," said Sir Colin Chandler, Vickers' chief executive. "We took 
it to the wire." 
</P>
<P>
 Chandler said Vickers could afford to design a new car, but that BMW's 
expertise would help create a new engine that would be able to meet exacting 
new environmental standards, particularly in Rolls' key U.S. market. 
</P>
<P>
 The Rover deal shocked Japanese car giant Honda, which had forged a 14-year 
relationship with Rover, lending its expertise and jointly developing two Rover 
lines. But it helped boost BMW's position, because Rover supplies body panels 
to Rolls. 
</P>
<P>
 "The fact that we have worked together was a contributing factor," Chandler 
told a news conference. BMW also supplies air bags and air-conditioning systems 
to Rolls-Royce. 
</P>
<P>
 The companies made it clear that the deal did not involve any immediate change 
in ownership of Rolls-Royce. 
</P>
<P>
 Chandler said an equity stake in Rolls-Royce was not currently an issue, but 
said he did not rule out anything in the long term. 
</P>
<P>
 The Rolls-BMW deal will also explore ways to develop the Concept Java car, a 
new high-performance Bentley coupe that has won praise from the automotive 
press. 
</P>
<P>
 BMW Chief Executive Bernd Pischetsrieder said that putting BMW engines in 
Rolls-Royces wouldn't dilute its strong brand or detract from its hand-crafted 
image. 
</P>
<P>
 "It is Rolls-Royce's and our opinion that another brand name must not appear 
in Rolls-Royce cars," he said. 
</P>
<P>
 Rolls-Royce said the deal would eventually mean the end of engine-building at 
the company, but that the 350 to 400 workers specializing in that area would be 
retrained and redeployed in other parts of the company. 
</P>
</TEXT>
