<TEXT>
<P>
 Art of the Kingdom: A couple who met, became engaged, and married at 
Disneyland have co-authored a photo book showing where to find various 
painting, carving, sculptures and other artifacts at the Magic Kingdom. 
</P>
<P>
 "Where in Disneyland Park" by Scott and Shani Wolf is being sold at Disney 
Stores, Disneyland and the new Walt Disney Gallery at MainPlace/Santa Ana.It 
retails for $9.95. 
</P>
<P>
 Scott Wolf, a onetime assistant producer of computer games for Disney Consumer 
Products in Burbank, met his future wife while she worked as a clerk at the 
Watch Shop on Main Street at Disneyland. They got married at the Disneyland 
Hotel exactly a year after their first date. 
</P>
<P>
 The couple said they got the idea for the book from noticing how many 
beautiful artworks there are inside the park. For instance, it shows a plaque 
engraved with a skull in New Orleans Square and a decorative peacock drawing at 
the Aladdin's Oasis dinner theater. The book's foreword was written by former 
Disneyland President Jack Lindquist. 
