<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: SANTA PAULA; TEEN-AGER DIES AFTER TRUCK CRASHES, 
BURNS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF McDONALD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Santa Paula teen-ager was killed when his truck crashed into a concrete 
culvert and burst into flames, the California Highway Patrol said. 
</P>
<P>
 Luis Huizar, 17, a farm worker from Mexico, was pronounced dead at the scene 
of the crash, which occurred about 12:15 a.m. Sunday on Telegraph Road east of 
Olive Road near Saticoy, a Ventura County coroner's official said. 
</P>
<P>
 Investigators said the pickup truck left the roadway for unknown reasons and 
crashed into a drainage ditch. The vehicle caught fire and Huizar died 
instantly, the CHP reported. 
</P>
<P>
 He was alone in the truck, investigators said. It is unclear whether Huizar 
was wearing his seat belt or whether alcohol or drugs played a part in the 
accident, the CHP said. 
</P>
<P>
 Huizar is survived by his parents in Mexico, the coroner's office said. JEFF 
McDONALD 
</P>
