EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: SIMI VALLEY; IN OPEN MEETING, COUNCIL OKS RAISES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SARA CATANIA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 One week after illegally granting pay increases for the city attorney and city 
manager behind closed doors, the Simi Valley City Council reconsidered the 
matter in open session Monday and approved the raises again. 
</P>
<P>
 City Manager Lin Koester will receive a 2.5% increase, boosting his total 
compensation by $3,946 to $187,199.City Atty. John Torrance will receive a 3.5% 
raise, increasing his pay and benefits by $4,142 to $147,186. The raises are 
effective immediately. 
</P>
<P>
 The council agreed to reconsider the matter in public after questions from The 
Times prompted Torrance to acknowledge that he had improperly advised the 
council to grant the raises. 
</P>
<P>
 Torrance said he was unaware of changes in the state open meeting law when he 
advised council members they could discuss and decide on such raises in private 
without informing the public in advance. SARA CATANIA 
