<HEADLINE>
<P>
HOSPITAL EXPANSION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The County Board of Supervisors has apparently decided to ignore the message 
from the last election, wherein the voters emphatically registered their 
opposition to government plans to borrow money to expand government's ability 
to provide services that could and should be provided by the free enterprise 
economy. 
</P>
<P>
 The supervisors added insult to injury when they voted to approve the 
$75-million county hospital expansion plan without waiting for the court to 
decide the pending suit filed by Community Memorial Hospital, to determine the 
legal role of a county-run hospital. 
</P>
<P>
 We will remember the names of the board members for the next election. But in 
the meantime, I hope more voters register their opinion. 
</P>
<P>
 RICHARD D. POAST 
</P>
<P>
 Oxnard 
