<HEADLINE>
<P>
MALATHION SPRAYING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Hysteria appears to be the response to the Medfly spraying in the Camarillo 
area. 
</P>
<P>
 The Medfly is not indigenous to California.It entered our state either with 
travelers, by mail or was illegally transported. If it becomes established, it 
will devastate commercial agriculture. We will all pay much more for fresh 
fruits and vegetables, and it will infect home-grown produce. It attacks more 
than 250 kinds of produce. 
</P>
<P>
 There is no "beneficial insect" to control the Medfly. Consequently, 
establishment of the Medfly in California would force pesticide spraying, which 
would kill all insects and jeopardize organic farming. 
</P>
<P>
 The use of minute amounts (1.2 ounces per acre) of malathion in infested areas 
will prevent a much higher use if the Medfly is allowed to proliferate. This 
pesticide has been used safely for over 40 years to control mosquitoes. 
</P>
<P>
 California leads the nation in total farm production. We cannot afford to let 
the Medfly become established. Use common sense to prevent contact with 
pesticides, but don't let hysteria and fear destroy California's crops. 
</P>
<P>
 GWEN ERICKSON 
</P>
<P>
 Ojai 
</P>
</TEXT>
