<P>
VALLEYWIDE FOCUS: AIRPORT LOT EXPECTED TO FILL UP QUICKLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MAKI BECKER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The holidays are traditionally the busiest time of year for the FlyAway bus 
service at Van Nuys Airport, and airport officials expect the terminal's 
parking lot to fill up quickly this week -- even as early as Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Officials recommend that travelers using the FlyAway bus service to Los 
Angeles International Airport have someone drop them off at the Van Nuys 
terminal, rather than parking their cars there.The terminal provides parking at 
$1 a day for about 2,000 vehicles. There is some overflow parking, "but even 
that gets filled up," said Van Nuys Airport spokeswoman Stacy Geere. 
</P>
<P>
 Buses head for the airport every 15 minutes between 5 and 8 a.m. and every 
half-hour between 8 a.m. and 1 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
 The FlyAway terminal is at 7610 Woodley Ave. in Van Nuys. For more 
information, call (818) 994-5554. MAKI BECKER 
</P>
