<HEADLINE>
<P>
3 TO BE CHARGED IN DRUG DEAL AT TOW YARD, POLICE SAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JULIE TAMAKI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Criminal charges are expected to be filed against three men who were shot and 
wounded over the weekend when a drug deal apparently turned sour at a Pacoima 
tow yard, Los Angeles police said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 Mariano Meza, 22; Candalerio Chaidez, 24, and Manuel Chaidez, 50, will face 
one count each of conspiracy to sell narcotics, Detective Frank Bishop said.All 
three were wounded shortly before noon Saturday after a gunfight erupted at the 
tow yard in the 9900 block of San Fernando Road near Montague Street. 
</P>
<P>
 Bishop said the dispute appeared to be over a drug sale. An estimated $90,000 
worth of cocaine was recovered at the scene as was an undisclosed amount of tar 
heroine, he said. 
</P>
<P>
 "They had the narcotics and somebody came in to take their drugs," Bishop 
said. "The guns came out and both sides started shooting." 
</P>
<P>
 Candalerio Chaidez was listed in good condition with bullet wounds to his arm 
and chest and Meza was also listed in good condition with a wound to his 
shoulder, Bishop said. Manuel Chaidez was listed in serious condition with 
multiple wounds to his upper body. 
</P>
<P>
 Police are investigating a fourth man, who turned up wounded at a local 
hospital, and has been listed in critical condition, Bishop said. As many as 
six other men are being sought in connection with the shooting. JULIE TAMAKI 
</P>
