<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY ROUNDUP: UCSB EXTENSION OFFERS MANAGEMENT SEMINARS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Jack Searles 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 UC Santa Barbara's Ventura Center will offer two seminars that are part of 
UCSB Extension's program in supervisory / management development during the 
winter quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 One of the courses, Understanding and Improving Communications, reviews the 
basic elements of the communication process and develops skills for 
communicating effectively in organizational environments.The instructor is 
David R. Seibold, a UCSB professor of communications. The one-day class meets 
from 9 a.m. to 4 p.m. Feb. 7. 
</P>
<P>
 The other Ventura seminar is Managing Creativity, designed to help 
participants free their imagination and apply the tools of creativity to any 
opportunity or challenge. The instructor, Edward H. Rockey, is a management 
consultant and trainer in Newbury Park. The class meets from 9 a.m. to 5 p.m. 
March 17. 
</P>
<P>
 A certificate of completion will be issued to those who satisfactorily 
complete six or more seminars in the series. 
</P>
<P>
 UCSB Extension is also offering a marketing sequence in the Santa Barbara area 
this winter. The sequence is being offered in cooperation with the Ventura, 
Conejo Valley and Santa Barbara chambers of commerce, along with the Santa 
Barbara Ad Club. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (805) 893-4200. 
</P>
</TEXT>
