<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY ROUNDUP: EDISON AWARDS OXNARD FIRM A CERTIFICATE OF MERIT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Jack Searles 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An Oxnard firm, Conrad & Okuma Architects, has been awarded a "Design for 
Excellence" certificate of merit by Southern California Edison.It was the 
second time in three years that the firm has been honored by Edison. 
</P>
<P>
 The certificate was awarded to Jeffrey S. Conrad and Albert A. Okuma for their 
renovation of Oxnard's main post office on C Street. 
</P>
<P>
 This year's competition drew more than 200 entries from industrial, commercial 
and educational projects. 
</P>
<P>
 Because of its energy-saving improvements, the post office project received a 
$24,000 rebate from Edison. 
</P>
<P>
 The renovation was praised for using glazed skylights to enhance natural 
lighting; high-efficiency, low-glare light fixtures; occupancy motion sensors; 
day lighting controls and high-efficiency heating, ventilating and 
air-conditioning units. 
</P>
</TEXT>
